{
  "texts": [
    "Participants (N = 469) were recruited from social media and university research pools and were randomly assigned to one of four agents.",
    "Three of the agents were social AIs that varied in their human likeness and mind capacity, and one was a human control, all named \"Ray. \"",
    "Banks tested implicit ascription of mind using five classic ToM tests that measure whether participants ascribe mind to an agent including the white lie scenario and the Sally-Anne test.",
    "Explicit measures of mind were measured by two questions: do you think Ray has a mind, and how confident are you in your response?",
    "For the implicit tests' open-ended responses, trained, independent raters coded the data for mentalistic explanations of behavior."
  ]
}